laboratory_examinations.findings: Gallbladder is distended with no pericholecystic fluid or gallbladder wall edema. The liver, spleen, kidneys, adrenal glands, pancreas are unremarkable. Notable findings include bilateral fat containing inguinal hernias and a fat-containing umbilical hernia, with mild atherosclerotic calcifications noted in the abdominal aorta. No suspicious lytic or sclerotic lesions.
